Breaking Kayfabe garnered strong reviews in Canadian, American and British media, and Cadence toured extensively to support the disc, including concerts across Canada and three shows in Austin, Texas at the 2006 South by Southwest festival.
Chart magazine named Cadence Weapon one of the 15 Canadian artists to watch in 2006.
In addition, the composite review site Metacritic listed Breaking Kayfabe as one of the best albums of 2006.
Cadence Weapon was nominated for the 2006 Polaris Music Prize, which awards $20,000 for the Canadian album of the year.
